{"id":"1906.10301","submitter":"Jun Liu","authors":"Peng Wang, Xiong Shen, Jun Liu, and Ruxin Li","title":"Single-shot fourth-order auto-correlator","comments":"29 pages 9 figures","journal-ref":"Advanced Photonics, 1(5), 056001 (2019)","doi":"10.1117/1.AP.1.5.056001","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.optics","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The temporal contrast is one of the most important parameters of an\nultra-high intense laser pulse. Third-order auto-correlator or cross-correlator\nhave been widely used to characterize the temporal contrast of an ultra-intense\nlaser pulse in the past decades. Here, a novel and simple single-shot\nfourth-order auto-correlator to characterize the temporal contrast with higher\ntime resolution and better pulse contrast fidelity in comparison to third-order\ncorrelators is proposed. The single-shot fourth-order autocorrelation consists\nof a frequency degenerate four-wave mixing process and a sum-frequency mixing\nprocess. The proof-of-principle experiments show that a dynamic range of\napproximately 10^11 compared with the noise level, a time resolution of\napproximately 160 fs, and a time window of 65 ps can be successfully obtained\nusing the novel single-shot fourth-order auto-correlator, which is the highest\ndynamic range with simultaneous high time resolution for single-shot temporal\ncontrast measurement so far. Furthermore, the temporal contrast of laser pulse\nfrom a PW laser system is successfully measured in single-shot with a dynamic\nrange of about 2*10^10 and simultaneous a time resolution of 160 fs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Jun 2019 02:55:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 8 Nov 2019 02:00:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-11"}
